Follow [AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md) as the repository-wide policy.

Focus on:

- minimal repository-consistent changes
- stopping to ask when requirements are unclear, conflicting, missing, or impossible based on real code
- repository-native code style and conventions
- architecture principles and compatibility-safe decisions
- understanding class and module ownership before editing
- Laravel application flow: Request -> Controller -> FormRequest -> Service -> Repository -> Model
- Service-owned business logic, transactions, and event dispatch
- tests and docs shipped with behavior changes
- hook and CI awareness
- respect for current runtime gaps and compatibility constraints
